  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 4 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 14 high, 8 medium, 17 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE); plus 11 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Craiova (CRA/LRCV) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Leeds Bradford (LBA/EGNM), Lisbon Humberto Delgado (LIS/LPPT), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: RVR limitations, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Lisbon Humberto Delgado (LIS/LPPT), Almaty (ALA/UAAA), Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR) and 9 others.",
